     1	# EDEN
     2	
     3	**E**ric's **D**irected **E**volution **N**exus — the meeting point where
     4	intelligent planning and evolutionary selection converge.
     5	
     6	## Tagline
     7	
     8	> Intelligent evolution.
     9	
    10	## Short description
    11	
    12	EDEN is a protocol for orchestrating directed code evolution, with an
    13	open reference implementation. Planners propose experiments, parallel trials
    14	run against a shared data model, results feed back into the next round — an
    15	automated loop of diversify, evaluate, amplify. Anyone can build a conforming
    16	planner, implementer, evaluator, or backing store in any language and
    17	interoperate with other conforming components.
    18	
    19	## Elevator pitch
    20	
    21	Most research automation tools are either a single-agent loop (try something,
    22	check if it worked, repeat) or a static job runner (execute a fixed matrix of
    23	experiments). EDEN is neither — and, importantly, EDEN is not a single system.
    24	It is a **protocol**: a specification that defines the roles (planner,
    25	implementer, evaluator, integrator), the messages they exchange, and the
    26	invariants they must honor. A conforming system coordinates concurrent
    27	research trials in which a planner — human, AI, or hybrid — proposes
    28	experiments, an integrator dispatches them against a versioned workspace,
    29	implementers modify code on isolated branches, and evaluators score the
    30	results against a fitness function. Results flow back to the planner to
    31	inform the next generation of proposals. The architecture mirrors directed
    32	evolution in the lab: generate a library of variants, screen them, amplify
    33	the winners, repeat.
    34	
    35	The repo is structured to house a **reference implementation** of the
    36	protocol, built up incrementally over the roadmap, plus a **conformance
    37	suite** that any independently-built component will be able to run
    38	against itself once the suite lands. The planner brings the
    39	intelligence; EDEN's contracts bring the infrastructure to run the
    40	search at scale, regardless of which implementation is plugged in
    41	where.
    42	
    43	## Etymology
    44	
    45	The name operates on two levels.
    46	
    47	**The acronym:** Eric's Directed Evolution Nexus — a nexus where experimental
    48	proposals, parallel execution, and evaluative selection meet. The system is the
    49	convergence point between a planner's intelligence and the outcomes of automated
    50	trials.
    51	
    52	**The allusion:** The Garden of Eden is where creation happens by design — an
    53	omniscient creator, a deliberate act. Directed evolution is the opposite: creation
    54	through iterative selection, not foresight. EDEN sits in the tension between
    55	these two ideas. The planner brings intent and strategy (intelligent design), but
    56	the mechanism is evolutionary — propose variants, run trials, select the fittest,
    57	repeat. The tagline "Intelligent evolution" captures this tension directly: it
    58	inverts "intelligent design," preserving the cadence but swapping the noun.
    59	
    60	## Scientific lineage
    61	
    62	Directed evolution is a Nobel Prize-winning technique (Frances Arnold, 2018)
    63	for engineering proteins through iterative cycles of diversification, screening,
    64	and amplification. A researcher generates a library of variants, evaluates them
    65	against a fitness function, and uses the best results as the template for the
    66	next round.
    67	
    68	The parallel to EDEN's architecture is nearly 1:1:
    69	
    70	| Directed Evolution          | EDEN                                        |
    71	| --------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
    72	| Library of variants         | Parallel trials in isolated git worktrees   |
    73	| Screening / assay           | Eval script producing JSON metrics          |
    74	| Amplification (next round)  | Planner reads results, proposes next batch  |
    75	| Iterative rounds            | The propose / execute / evaluate loop       |
    76	| Mutagenesis                 | Planner proposes modifications to the code  |
    77	| Intelligent guidance        | Planner is strategic, not random            |
    78	
    79	## Package name (reference implementation, planned)
    80	
    81	The Python reference implementation **will be published** as `direvo`
    82	(**dir**ected **evo**lution) once it exists (landing in Phase 3 per
    83	`docs/roadmap.md`). Both `direvo` and `eden` will work as CLI commands
    84	after install — users can think of the tool as EDEN while the package
    85	name stays short, unique, and conflict-free.
    86	
    87	```bash
    88	# After Phase 3 lands, installation will look like:
    89	pip install direvo
    90	eden run --config .eden/config.yaml
    91	```
    92	
    93	The name "eden" is heavily used across the software ecosystem (Eden AI,
    94	Eden emulator, multiple PyPI packages), making it impractical as a
    95	package name. The dual-name strategy avoids all registry conflicts while
    96	giving users the brand name at the command line.
    97	
    98	This naming applies to the Python reference implementation only.
    99	Third-party implementations in other languages / ecosystems are free to
   100	choose their own names and should not use `direvo` or `eden` without
   101	coordination; the protocol version they target (e.g. `eden-protocol/v0`)
   102	is the identity that matters for interoperability.
   103	
   104	## Availability check — `direvo`
   105	
   106	Historical name-squatting check carried over from the predecessor
   107	project. Re-verify before actually publishing in Phase 3+.
   108	
   109	| Registry    | Name   | Status as of 2025-03-27 |
   110	| ----------- | ------ | ----------------------- |
   111	| PyPI        | direvo | Available               |
   112	| GitHub user | direvo | Available               |
   113	| GitHub org  | direvo | Available               |
   114	| npm         | direvo | Available               |

