     1	# AGENTS.md
     2	
     3	This file provides guidance to AI agents working with this repository.
     4	
     5	## What this repo is
     6	
     7	EDEN is a **protocol** for directed-code-evolution orchestration, not a
     8	single product. The repo contains three distinct kinds of artifact, each
     9	with different change discipline:
    10	
    11	| Layer | Path | Authoritative? | Change discipline |
    12	|---|---|---|---|
    13	| Protocol specification | [`spec/`](spec/) | Yes — the source of truth | RFC-style: versioned, normative (MUST/SHOULD/MAY), carefully reviewed |
    14	| Reference implementation | [`reference/`](reference/) | No — *one* valid impl | Normal code-review discipline |
    15	| Conformance suite | [`conformance/`](conformance/) | Normative for tests | Black-box; must be implementation-agnostic |
    16	
    17	Non-normative human docs live in [`docs/`](docs/).
    18	
    19	## Current phase
    20	
    21	**Phase 0 (bootstrap) in progress.** Scaffolding is in place; the
    22	remaining steps (commit, push, branch protection) finish the phase.
    23	No code yet. See [`docs/roadmap.md`](docs/roadmap.md) for the full
    24	13-phase plan. The spec itself is not yet written —
    25	[`spec/v0/README.md`](spec/v0/README.md) lists the planned chapters
    26	with their target phases.
    27	
    28	## Commands
    29	
    30	At Phase 0 only markdown linting is in play.
    31	
    32	| Command | Purpose |
    33	|---|---|
    34	| `npx --yes markdownlint-cli2@0.14.0 "**/*.md" "#node_modules" "#.venv" "#docs/archive/**" "#docs/plans/review/**"` | Lint all tracked markdown (pinned to CI's version; matches CI exactly) |
    35	
    36	### Commands that will exist in later phases
    37	
    38	These are listed for orientation; none of the tooling is wired up yet.
    39	
    40	| Command | Lands in |
    41	|---|---|
    42	| `uv sync` | Phase 3 (first `pyproject.toml`) |
    43	| `uv run ruff check .` | Phase 3 |
    44	| `uv run pyright` | Phase 3 |
    45	| `uv run pytest -q` | Phase 3 |
    46	| `check-jsonschema --schemafile ...` | Phase 1 (first JSON Schema) |
    47	| Schema ↔ Pydantic parity check | Phase 3 |
    48	| `docker compose up` end-to-end | Phase 10 |
    49	
    50	## Contribution conventions
    51	
    52	### Spec edits
    53	
    54	+ Every cross-component contract (wire format, state machine, invariant)
    55	  is defined in `spec/` first, then implemented in `reference/`. When
    56	  they disagree, the spec wins and the impl gets a bug.
    57	+ Spec chapters use RFC 2119 language: MUST, SHOULD, MAY.
    58	+ Spec versions are frozen once stable (`spec/v0/` is a single lineage;
    59	  breaking changes go to `spec/v1/`).
    60	+ Schema changes must update the spec prose, the JSON Schema file, and
    61	  (from Phase 3 onward) the Pydantic bindings in lockstep. CI will
    62	  enforce schema ↔ model parity once both exist.
    63	
    64	### Reference implementation
    65	
    66	+ Normal code-review discipline.
    67	+ Normative behavior is tested against the conformance suite (once it
    68	  exists in Phase 11).
    69	+ The reference impl is explicitly not a monopoly on correctness. A
    70	  third-party implementation that passes conformance is equally valid.
    71	
    72	## Commit guidelines
    73	
    74	+ Short imperative subjects (e.g., "Add event protocol chapter",
    75	  "Pin task state machine").
    76	+ For pull requests, include: what the change is, which phase it
    77	  advances, and any spec ↔ impl implications.
    78	
    79	## Related docs
    80	
    81	+ [`docs/naming.md`](docs/naming.md) — what EDEN is, at the concept level.
    82	+ [`docs/roadmap.md`](docs/roadmap.md) — the 13-phase build-up plan with
    83	  unit-level decomposition.
    84	+ [`docs/plans/`](docs/plans/) — active implementation plans.
    85	+ [`docs/archive/`](docs/archive/) — historical reference docs.
    86	+ [`STYLE_GUIDE.md`](STYLE_GUIDE.md) — formatting and naming conventions.
    87	+ [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](CONTRIBUTING.md) — setup and PR workflow.

